#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.head.title:12-1
msgid "Additional Notes onLaptop Keystrokes for Reading Text and Information"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h1:17-1
msgid "Additional Notes on Laptop Keystrokes for Reading Text and Information"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:18-1
msgid "General Notes"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:19-1
msgid ""
"Most of the keystrokes for reading text move the active cursor to the "
"beginning of the text being read. Keystrokes for reading the current "
"character, line, word, sentence, or paragraph do not move the active cursor. "
"Most of these keystrokes work in all cursor modes. The JAWS and Invisible "
"cursor can only read text already on the screen; they cannot scroll a "
"document in the manner the PC cursor or Virtual PC cursor can."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:20-1
msgid "Keystroke Specific Notes"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:21-1
msgid "Say Character Phonetically (CAPS LOCK+COMMA twice quickly)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:22-1
msgid ""
"After pressing this keystroke, <b>CAPS LOCK+M</b> says the prior character "
"phonetically and <b>CAPS LOCK+PERIOD</b> says the next character "
"phonetically until some other keystroke is pressed. This keystroke works in "
"all cursor modes."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:23-1
msgid "Say ASCII or Hexadecimal Value (CAPS LOCK+COMMA three times quickly)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:24-1
msgid ""
"This keystrokes reads the ASCII value of the current character. If you want "
"to hear the hexadecimal value of the current character instead, select the "
"Speak Character Value in Hex check box in the Images and Symbols group in "
"Settings Center."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:25-1
msgid "Spell Word (CAPS LOCK+K twice quickly)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:26-1
msgid ""
"After pressing this keystroke, <b>CAPS LOCK+J</b> spells the prior word and "
"<b>CAPS LOCK+L</b> spells the next word until some other keystroke is "
"pressed. This keystroke works in all cursor modes."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:27-1
msgid "Say to Cursor (CAPS LOCK+SHIFT+J)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:28-1
msgid ""
"Any text to the left of, and on the same line as, the active cursor is read. "
"This keystroke works in all cursor modes. This keystroke does not move the "
"active cursor."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:29-1
msgid "Say from Cursor (CAPS LOCK+SHIFT+L)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:30-1
msgid ""
"Any text to the right of, and on the same line as, the active cursor is "
"read. This keystroke works in all cursor modes. This keystroke does not move "
"the active cursor."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:31-1
msgid "Say All (CAPS LOCK+A or CAPS LOCK+DOWN ARROW)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:32-1
msgid ""
"When in JAWS or Invisible Cursor modes, this keystroke stops reading when "
"the text currently displayed on the screen has been read, or when "
"interrupted. When in PC or Virtual PC Cursor modes, this keystroke reads to "
"the end of the current document, or until interrupted."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:33-1
msgid "Say Top Line of Window (CAPS LOCK+SHIFT+Y)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:34-1
msgid ""
"This keystroke may have different results in different applications. In some "
"programs, it reads the title bar, while in others it may read the menus or "
"toolbars at the top of the window."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:35-1
msgid "Say Bottom Line of Window (CAPS LOCK+SHIFT+N)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cllaptop_keystrokes_for_reading_text_an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:36-1
msgid ""
"This keystroke reads the bottom line of a window, which is normally where a "
"status bar is located."
msgstr ""

